#T_RL=webanno.custom.Coref|type|BT_webanno.custom.Referent
#Text=What is a new goal ?
#Text=Balance .
#Text=Trying to grow my career enough to make sure it does n’t consume me .
#Text=It ’s hard to balance a touring career because there is no structure to your life .
#Text=I ’m trying to take this dream and make it work as a job .
#Text=How challenging is it to obtain that in the folk world ?
#Text=There ’s not a lot of money in the folk world .
#Text=In generally right now I think people ’s numbers are down and only a few people can make a living at it .
#Text=It ’s pretty competitive .
#Text=I ’m doing okay , but there ’s no huge riches in it so I ’m trying to think of my future and maintain a balance in it .
#Text=Do you think of doing something less folk-oriented to give your career a push ?
#Text=Not really , I ’ve done that a little bit by trying to approach the major labels , but that was when the major labels were dying so I came in at a bad time for that .
#Text=I found that when it comes to do it yourself , the folk world is the best place to make money because as soon as you go major you are paying a band .
#Text=More money
#Text=more problems .
#Text=More money , more investing .
#Text=It ’s a hard question .
#Text=What things did you encounter doing a studio album that you had not foreseen ?
#Text=Giving up control is hard when you have a producer .
#Text=His vision , sometimes , is something you ca n’t understand and have to trust sometimes .
#Text=See how it comes out .
#Text=That was hard for me , because up until now I have been such a do it yourself , writing my own songs , recording them myself .
#Text=What is your most treasured possession ?
#Text=I ’d like to say my guitar , but I ’m still looking for a good one .
#Text=I have this little latex glove . [ Laughs ]
#Text=It ’s a long story —
#Text=Please !
#Text=Do tell !
#Text=When I was in college I had a romantic friend named David , he was kind of my first love .
#Text=We were young and found this latex glove in a parking lot .
#Text=We though , “ Oh , this is a nice glove , we ’ll name him Duncan . ”
#Text=You found a latex glove in a parking lot and you decided to take it ?
#Text=Yeah [ Laughs ] .
#Text=He became the symbol of our friendship .
#Text=He ’s disgusting at this point , he ’s falling apart .
#Text=But David and I are still friends and we ’ll pass him back and forth to each other every three years or so when we ’ve forgotten his existence .
#Text=David surprised me at a show in Philly .
#Text=He gave Duncan to the sound man who brought it back stage , and now I have Duncan .
#Text=So he ’s kind of special to me .
